    "title": "Cell",
    "description": "The cell represents the basic unit of Life. Cells can act as rigid scaffolds, fluid blobs, diaphanous sheets, roving sentries, quiescent spores, invading barbarians, detoxification centers, advanced chemical laboratories, long- or short-term storage depots, solar panels, multi-modal sensory arrays, wetware computers, protection from the elements, study systems, studying systems, complex input/output devices, contractile catapults, templates for future life, or superconductive electrical wires - some of which You are using to read this paragraph.",
